## 1. Threat Model\
\
We assume the following attack vectors and design our architecture to mitigate them:\
\
| Attack Vector | Description | Mitigation |\
| :--- | :--- | :--- |\
| **Physical tampering** | Attacker accesses Sentinel Rig to modify data or extract cryptographic keys | ATECC608A secure element with tamper detection; keys never exposed; hardware kill-switch |\
| **Network interception** | Attacker captures or modifies data in transit | MQTT over TLS 1.3 with mutual authentication; payload encryption |\
| **Cloud compromise** | Attacker gains access to backend servers | Hash chain enables independent verification; cloud keys separate from edge keys |\
| **Fake rig injection** | Attacker attempts to submit data from unauthorised devices | Mutual TLS with certificate revocation; hardware root of trust |\
| **Replay attack** | Attacker resends previously captured valid data | Timestamp + monotonic counter in each packet; backend rejects out-of-order packets |\
\
