## 2. Cryptographic Guarantees\
\
### 2.1 At the Edge (Sentinel Rig)\
\
| Component | Specification |\
| :--- | :--- |\
| **Secure Element** | ATECC608A with hardware-accelerated SHA-256 |\
| **Key Generation** | Private keys generated inside secure element, never exposed |\
| **Key Storage** | Protected storage with physical tamper detection |\
| **Signing** | Every 30-second data packet signed with SHA-256 |\
| **Anti-Replay** | Timestamp + monotonic counter in each packet |\
| **Tamper Response** | Physical tamper pins trigger key zeroisation |\
\
### 2.2 In Transit\
\
| Layer | Mechanism |\
| :--- | :--- |\
| **Transport Security** | MQTT over TLS 1.3 with mutual authentication |\
| **Certificate Management** | Short-lived certificates (30 days) from private PKI |\
| **Payload Encryption** | AES-256-GCM on top of TLS (defence in depth) |\
\
### 2.3 At Rest\
\
| Location | Mechanism |\
| :--- | :--- |\
| **Local Storage (SD card)** | AES-256 encrypted, key stored in ATECC608A |\
| **Cloud Storage** | Server-side encryption with customer-managed keys |\
| **Backup** | Cryptographic hash chain enables verification of backup integrity |\
\
